body: "## Context\npm validate --check-files currently reports validate_files_missing_linked_paths:146 and validate_files_orphaned_paths:134. Source/test relocations (cli-contracts split PR#396, module-mirrored test reorg 2026-06-16, all-src <2000 LOC splits 2026-05-25, SDK bundle move pm-4oww) moved files out from under their linked-file rows, and newer modules were created without owners.\n\n## Approach\n1. Missing paths (146): for each linked row whose path no longer exists, find the successor file(s) (git log --follow) and re-point the row via pm files commands on the owning item — do NOT hand-edit .toon storage.\n2. Orphaned paths (134): assign each unowned src/tests file to the item that delivered it (git blame → PR → pm id from session memory/CHANGELOG links); files with no traceable owner go to the owning capability epic.\n3. Batch by directory; record before/after warning counts as comments here.\n\n## Definition of done\nBoth validate --check-files counters at (or near) zero with every remaining exception justified in a comment; spot-check that `pm files` on touched items renders valid paths."
